text:
I have been working with a client on a VERY custom husbpot development and I am struggling with an issue specific to the date time picker displaying times in the wrong timezone.

A workaround that I am currently using is using a yes/no for daylight savings with conditional adjustments:

      {% if  content.widgets.module_16330990089562.body.daylight=="Yes" %}
      {{ content.widgets.module_16330990089562.body.pre_sale |minus_time(6, 'hours') |datetimeformat('%b %d, %Y, %l:%M %p')  }}
      {% elif content.widgets.module_16330990089562.body.daylight=="No" %}
      {{ content.widgets.module_16330990089562.body.pre_sale |minus_time(7, 'hours') |datetimeformat('%b %d, %Y, %l:%M %p')  }}
      {% endif %}

However, the client doesn't want to have to select yes or no for the DST and wants it intuitively pull from the timezone set in the account (trust me, I do too lol)

Has anyone encountered this and know a solution?
